                            <comment id="13675552" author="mavrukin" created="Wed, 5 Jun 2013 03:04:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=talevy&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;talevy&quot;&gt;Tal Levy&lt;/a&gt; thanks for this commit, looks really useful!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13681784" author="klotz" created="Thu, 13 Jun 2013 00:07:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Codegen lets you prevent the creation of data messages that don&apos;t correspond to the schema.  Using a Python dict turns that error into a runtime error.  This gives you the ability to detect data validation errors earlier.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13738579" author="cutting" created="Tue, 13 Aug 2013 18:01:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This looks great.  Tests pass for me.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A few concerns I have before we commit this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Can we please avoid incompatibly changing the command line for SpecificCompilerTool?  Perhaps we should add a -lang option that defaults to &apos;java&apos;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Shouldn&apos;t we add some tests of the generated Python code?  We might just add tests in the python tree that refer to ../../lang/java/tools/src/test/compiler/output/*.py, or we could move these into share/test.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We might add something to the Python &quot;getting started&quot; guide about this.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13747214" author="talevy" created="Thu, 22 Aug 2013 04:19:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the comments&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;I will make the backwards compatibility update to the SpecificCompilerTool and re-submit the patch&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;I agree, python tests for the codegen would be nice. Making the tests will be straightforward. Does it make sense to only move the python test/compiler/output to a shared directory, while leaving the rest in there? feels disconnected. Would it be possible to have the ant-build script codegen something from share/test, like share/test/schemas/weather.avsc, and then add that to the python path for testing?&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;After the python test plan is set up, I can write something up for the getting started on how to use it.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
